usstsein unumgänglich ist, historische Differenz und mediale Filter wahrzunehmen und deren Effekte zu reflektieren.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aEuropäische Geschichte. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aGesellschaft. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMediale Repräsentation. 4aMittelalter. 4aPublic History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aCultural History.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aEarly Modernity.  aEuropean History.  aHistory.  aMedia Representation.  aMemory Culture.  aMiddle Age.  aPublic History.  aSociety.1 aAuffarth, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsposito, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFebel, Gisela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFebel, Gisela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFulda, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKerth, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKerth, Sonja, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKuhlmann, Hauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLienert, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLienert, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMaassen, Irmgard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiedema, Nine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOswalt, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4htt